Group Managing Director Of the Nigerian National Petroleum Corporation (NNPC), Mele Kyari, has stated that fuel scarcity is being sorted out as distribution is now going on. He disclosed this while speaking to reporters on Sunday, stating that the the situation in Lagos and Abuja have greatly improved. “We are resolving our issues, supply is robust, distribution is being sorted, support from partners and stakeholders massive, seeking further understanding of Nigerians as we move towards normalcy. Confusion As Pro-Tinubu Governors Takeover APC CECPC JUST IN: Yoruba Nation Activist, Sunday Ighoho Released “We are happy normalcy is returning, we are loading products all over the country, truck numbers are increasing, normalcy is returning gradually. “We have seen the situation in Lagos and Abuja have greatly improved. We are very sure that normalcy will return very soon that is why we are here to ensure that normalcy returns to our country. And also, what is very true is that Mr President is constantly in pictures of what is happening, he is updated every moment, he is giving us all the direction and stir and support that we require. We are very happy with the support we are Getty from him including the Minister of Petroleum,” Kyari said.